Types of Repositories 
●	Bare Repository (Center Repo.)
1.	Store and share only
2.	All central repositories are Bare Repo.
3.	GitHub & GitLab are Bare Repository / Center Repo.

●	Non – Bare Repository (Local Repo.)
1.	Where you can modify files
2.	All local repositories are non-bare Repo

Commands need to run once the Linux AWS machine has been created.
●	sudo su
●	yum update -y
●	yum install git -y
●	git – version
●	git config  --global user.name “zaved”
●	git config  --global user.email zaved.python@hotmail.com
●	git config –list

Commit | Push | Pull 

●	Login in Mumbai EC2 Instance 
●	Create a directory and go inside it.
●	Git init.
●	Git status
●	Touch myfile (Put some data inside the file)
●	Git status  (To know the untrack file/code in the working space area)
●	Git add .    (To add code into staging area)
●	Git commit -m “1st commit from Mumbai”
●	Git status
●	Git log   
●	Git log -1 / git log -2
●	Git log --oneline 
●	Git log –grep “keyword”
●	Git show <commit id>

●	Git remote add origin <central git URL>
●	Git push -u origin master
●	Enter username & password

●	Login in Singapore EC2 Instance 
●	Create a directory and go inside it.
●	Git init.
●	Git remote add origin “central git URL”
●	Git pull origin master
●	Git log
●	Git show <commit id>
●	Add some code.
●	Git status  (To know the untrack file/code in the working space area)
●	Git add .
●	Git commit -m “1st commit from Mumbai”
●	Git status
●	Git log
●	Git show <commit id>
●	Git push -u origin master

To ignore some files while commenting 

1.	Create one hidden file     . gitignore and enter file format which you want to ignore.
2.	Vi   .gitignore
3.	Enter 	*.css
*.py
*.txt
4.	git add .gitignore  (Add this file into staging area)
5.	git commit -m “latest update exclude .css”
6.	git status

Create some .txt .java & .css files and add them running “git add”. E;g touch file.txt,file1.txt,file3.java,file4.css.

ls
git status
git add
git status
git commit -m “my txt files only ”


